		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">design a full system from scratch is, IMHO, a form a art</div><br />I agree, however this doesn't make programing an art.<br /><br />Programing inself is not an art, but it can be seen a tool to do art. Like math, which is just a tool that can be used for other purposes.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">And you don't even need to use X when reading the controller anyway; you can use the result variable itself as the counter. Now that's art, if I do say so myself.</div>
<br />I disagree. A clever optimization is not art. That being said, a good video game would be a piece of art even without this kind of clever optimisation, even with goofy unoptimized high-level code.

		

